NFL field goal attempts: modeling the long shots

James R Bland (https://sites.google.com/site/jamesbland/)

November 25, 2019

A few days ago, I estimated a 1-parameter model of NFL field goal attempts using data from pro-football-reference.com. While it did reasonably well for most distances, it was especially terrible for the long shots (\(>60\) yards), so today I will add another two parameters to hopefully model these a bit better.

H/T to Will Harrison (@willjharrison) for suggesting this!

The new part of the model

A player makes a field goal attempt \(x\) yards from the goal (my data). The goal posts are \(d\) yards apart (given),

I alluded to a slightly more complicated version of this in the previous post. Here, I assume that players range (how far they can kick the ball and still have it go over the horizontal bar) is distributed \(N(m,s)\), so the probability of making the distance is \(1-\Phi((x-m)/s)\). Hence, the probability of a successful field goal attempt at \(x\) yards from goal is: \[ \Pr\left(\text{angle good} \mid x,\kappa,m,s\right)=\underbrace{\left(1-\Phi((x-m)/s)\right)}_{\text{distance}}\underbrace{\left(1-2\Phi\left(\kappa^{-1}\cos^{-1}\left(\frac{x}{\sqrt{x^2+d^2/4}}\right)\right)\right)}_\text{angle (my old model)} \]

I assign an informative prior over \(m\) so that this effect can only be important for long distances. Specifically: \(m\sim N(60,3)\). Note that for the distance component of the model, the probability is declining fastest at \(x=m\).

Estimating the model in Stan

// FieldGoalsCountDistance.stan
functions {
   
              
}
data {
  // Tell Stan how to read in the data
  int n; // Number of observations
  real d; 
  int  y[n]; // =count of scored
  int  N[n]; // number of attempts from that distance
  vector[n]  Distance; //
  real priorK[2];
  real priorM[2];
  real priorS;
  
}
transformed data {
    
}
parameters {
  real<lower=0> k;
  real m;
  real<lower=0> s;

}
transformed parameters {
  
}
model {
    vector[n] pAngle;
    vector[n] pDistance;
    vector[n] p;
    for (ii in 1:n) {
        pAngle[ii] =  1-2*normal_cdf(-acos(Distance[ii]/sqrt(Distance[ii]^2+d^2/4.0)),0.0,k);
        pDistance[ii] = max({1.0-normal_cdf(Distance[ii],m,s),0.000001});
        p[ii] = pAngle[ii]*pDistance[ii];
    }   

  k ~ lognormal(priorK[1],priorK[2]);
  m ~ normal(priorM[1],priorM[2]);
  s ~ exponential(priorS);
  y ~ binomial(N,p);


  }
generated quantities {
    
}

AggData<-aggregate(Data[,c("Dist","Y","B")],by=list(Data$Dist),FUN=mean)
#
AggData$count<-aggregate(Data[,c("Dist")], by=list(Data$Dist),FUN=length)$x
AggData<-AggData[AggData$Dist<=65,]
#
  k<-extract(FitALL)$k
  m<-extract(FitALL)$m
  s<-extract(FitALL)$s
  x<-seq(1,80)
  angle<-acos(x/sqrt(x^2+d^2/4))
  pltData<-data.frame()
  for (xx in 1:length(x)) {
    pAngle<-1-2*pnorm(-angle[xx]/k)
    pDistance<-1-pnorm((x[xx]-m)/s)
    pTotal<-pAngle*pDistance
    
    p<-pAngle
    tmp<-data.frame(p)
    tmp$x<-x[xx]
    tmp$prob<-"Angle"
    pltData<-rbind(pltData,tmp)
    p<-pDistance
    tmp<-data.frame(p)
    tmp$x<-x[xx]
    tmp$prob<-"Distance"
    pltData<-rbind(pltData,tmp)
    p<-pTotal
    tmp<-data.frame(p)
    tmp$x<-x[xx]
    tmp$prob<-"Total"
    pltData<-rbind(pltData,tmp)
  }
  pltD<-aggregate(pltData,by=list(pltData$x,pltData$prob),FUN=mean)
  pltD$prob<-pltD$Group.2
  pltD$pl<-aggregate(pltData$p,by=list(pltData$x,pltData$prob),FUN='quantile',probs=0.025)$x
  pltD$pu<-aggregate(pltData$p,by=list(pltData$x,pltData$prob),FUN='quantile',probs=0.975)$x
  
  
  plt<-ggplot(pltD,aes(x=x,y=p))+geom_line(size=2,aes(color=prob))+geom_ribbon(aes(ymin=pl,ymax=pu,fill=prob),alpha=0.2,linetype="blank")
  plt<-plt+geom_point(data=AggData,aes(x=Dist,y=Y,size=count),alpha=0.5)
  plt<-plt+xlab("Distance to goal (yards)")+ylab("Probability of success")+theme_bw()
  plt

Here I plot the two components of the model separately (angle and distance), as well as the total prediction, which is equal to their product.

APPENDIX: estimating the models in R

#FieldGoals_EstimateBinomialDistance.R

rm(list=ls()) 
setwd("C:/Users/jbland/OneDrive - University of Toledo/General notes on structural Bayes/Sports")
library(foreign)
library(xtable)
library(ggplot2)
library(gganimate)
library(gifski)
library(png)
library("rstan") # observe startup messages
rstan_options(auto_write = TRUE)
Sys.setenv(LOCAL_CPPFLAGS = '-march=native')
options(mc.cores = parallel::detectCores())



Data<-data.frame(read.csv("C:/Users/jbland/OneDrive - University of Toledo/General notes on structural Bayes/Sports/FieldGoalsDataScrape.csv"))
Data$Y<-as.integer(Data$Good=="Y")
Data$B<-as.integer(Data$Blk=="Y")
Data$year<-as.integer(format(as.Date(Data$Date), "%Y"))
Data$month<-as.integer(format(as.Date(Data$Date), "%m"))
Data$season<-Data$year-as.integer(Data$month<=8)

# remove blocked attempts
Data<-Data[Data$B==0,]

# Distance between goal posts 18 feet 6 inches
d<-18.5/3

Data$Angle<-acos(Data$Dist/sqrt(Data$Dist^2+d^2/4))

## ALL ATTEMPTS

D<-Data 
DCount<-aggregate(D,by=list(D$Dist),FUN=length)
N<-DCount$Y
y<-aggregate(D,by=list(D$Dist),FUN=mean)$Y*N
Angle<-aggregate(D,by=list(D$Dist),FUN=mean)$Angle
Distance<-aggregate(D,by=list(D$Dist),FUN=mean)$Dist
StanData<-list(d=d,Distance=Distance,y=as.integer(y),N=N,n=length(Angle),priorK=c(log(pi),pi/8),priorM=c(60,3),priorS=1)
FitALL<-stan("FieldGoalsCountDistance.stan",data=StanData,seed=42)
saveRDS(FitALL, "NFLFieldGoalsData/NFLFieldGoalsALLDistance.rds")


# By Season
if (TRUE) {
SeasonList<-unique(Data$season)
SimSeason<-data.frame()
for (ss in 1:length(SeasonList)) {
  D<-Data[Data$season==SeasonList[ss],]
  DCount<-aggregate(D,by=list(D$Dist),FUN=length)
  N<-DCount$Y
  y<-aggregate(D,by=list(D$Dist),FUN=mean)$Y*N
  Angle<-aggregate(D,by=list(D$Dist),FUN=mean)$Angle
  Distance<-aggregate(D,by=list(D$Dist),FUN=mean)$Dist
  StanData<-list(d=d,Distance=Distance,y=as.integer(y),N=N,n=length(Angle),priorK=c(log(pi),pi/8),priorM=c(60,3),priorS=1)
  Fit<-stan("FieldGoalsCountDistance.stan",data=StanData,seed=42,control = list(adapt_delta = 0.999))
  k<-extract(Fit, permuted = TRUE)$k
  m<-extract(Fit)$m
  s<-extract(Fit)$s
  tmp<-data.frame(k,m,s)
  tmp$season<-SeasonList[ss]
  SimSeason<-rbind(SimSeason,tmp)
  print(paste("---",SeasonList[ss],"---",ss,"of",length(SeasonList)))
} 
saveRDS(SimSeason,"NFLFieldGoalsData/SimSeasonDistance.rds")
}
